liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Here's how Wales/Cymru lineup, with Warren Gatland going back to the same team that beat Fiji in their tournament opener. That means there's no space in the 23 for co-captain Dewi Lake. Adam Beard is set to win his 50th cap at lock. "We're happy with our position going into this game," Wales coach Gatland said, with a win all-but guaranteeing Wales top spot in the group. "Australia have talented players and we know they will want to come out and put in a performance. "We know we have to take our chances and put them under as much pressure as possible. "If we play the way we know we can and maintain that for 80 minutes, we will be a very hard team to beat. "They're going to be desperate, we're desperate as well. "I expect us to win on Sunday."
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Wales lineup
